               <head>
                  <title type="uniform">Strengleikar</title>, <title xml:lang="is">Grelent</title>;
            <origPlace>Norway</origPlace>, <origDate notBefore="1260" notAfter="1280">c.
            1270</origDate>.<note>The manuscript consists of four fragments discovered by <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> in the lining of a bishop's mitre
            at <name type="place" key="Skálh01">Skálholt</name> in <name type="place" key="Icela01" xml:lang="en">Iceland</name> in <date when="1703">1703</date>. It once belonged to
            the codex now catalogued as <title type="ms">Codex De la Gardie 4-7</title> in the <name type="org">The University Library</name>, <name type="place" key="Uppsa01">Uppsala</name> (<name type="org" xml:lang="sv">Uppsala universitetsbibliotek</name>)<!--REFERENCE TO PICTURE 91 (THE MITRE IN ONE PIECE)-->.</note>
               </head>
